The paper deals with the problem of coordinated multi-cell beamforming in massive MIMO systems, which involves the use of information theory, networking, signal processing, and optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of random matrix theory, which falls under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of power savings, which is related to game theory, and hence cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a possible category.
